  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "A big change is that it doesn't allow inputting arbitrary api parameters from the URL bar, which I think is a great idea, especially from a security POV, but I'm slightly wondering which usecases will be broken by not allowing refinement from arbitrary elements from the URL. \r\n\r\nDynamic widgets might also be interesting to consider, I think it's fine here, where the URL is basically the source of truth, so widgets could be created, simply by being there in the URL, others could be left empty. I think this is a step forward for that direction and won't impede future explorations regarding dynamic behaviour.",
