    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@Haroenv in `urlSync`, the configuration could be as follow:\r\n```\r\nmapping: {\r\n  q: 'search',\r\n  fR: 'features',\r\n  dFR: 'choices',\r\n}\r\n```\r\nbut this is still an issue for nested values like the `dFR` one: `[url]?dFR[choice_features.Power supply][0]=Battery&dFR[choice_features.Brand][0]=Samsung`\r\n\r\nSo I was thinking similar but more nested, like:\r\n```\r\nmapping: {\r\n  q: 'search',\r\n  fR: 'features',\r\n  dFR: {\r\n    choice_features: {\r\n      'Brand': 'brand',\r\n      'Power supply': 'power-supply',\r\n    },\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhich would give: `[url]?power-supply=Battery&brand=Samsung`.\r\n\r\nIs there an ETA for this PoC? If not, is this possible to customize the url and title in [vue instantseach](https://github.com/algolia/vue-instantsearch)? (the only alternative I'm willing to give a shot).",
