  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Some thoughts on naming:\r\n- I would call the modern storage \"history\". What may seem modern for us might just be the standard for everyone else. And that's the API being used behind\r\n- I would go for page = 1 right now so that the full UI (url, view) now has the same page, which is 1\r\n- proposal API for discussion/bike shedding:\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\ninstantsearch({\r\n  router: {\r\n    storage: instantsearch.router.history({\r\n      windowTitle() {},\r\n      createURL() {},\r\n      parseURL() {}\r\n    }),\r\n    mapping: {\r\n      uIStateToRouteState() {}\r\n      routeStateToUiState() {}\r\n    }\r\n    // also feasible: mapping: instantsearch.router.mapping.default\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. rename urlSync2 to router\r\n2. rename instantsearch.storage to instantsearch.router\r\n3. rename modern to history\r\n4. rename UIStateMapping to mapping\r\n5. rename toSyncable to routeStateToUiState\r\n6. from Syncable to uIStateToRouteState\r\n\r\nI found syncable to/from hard to grasp by default and thought this was a shared appreciation from the team in the meeting (we even made the mistake on the schemas if I remember well)\r\n\r\nAs for the storage API I have no change to propose BUT maybe \"write\", it seems to only be called at page load time, should we call it \"onInit\" rather than read? Not sure about this one, it's maybe just documentation and maybe in some situations it will be called \r\n\r\nAs for having a \"better\" default mapping as proposed by Haroen, I am sure this can come later on and live under instantsearch.router.mapping.clean.\r\n\r\n(Again, this is a proposal to discuss)",
